---
title: Big Batch Soy-Sesame Chicken & Broccoli 2x the delicious portions!
description: These wholesome, family-friendly rice bowls are packed with juicy chicken thighs, tender broccoli, bok choy, and napa cabbage flavored with nutty sesame oil and tossed in a rich, savory soy-hoisin sauce. Serve this flavorful feast family style, garnished with crackly sesame seeds for a crunchy finishing touch.

*This recipe is double the typical servings, providing 4 servings and 8 servings for a 2 person and 4 person box respectively.*

image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/669ecf1b46ae2b14647c3c9d-71e8e309.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/669ecf1b46ae2b14647c3c9d-en-US.pdf
servings: 2
time required: 45 minutes
course: main course
cuisine: Southeast Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 710 kcal
  fat: 22 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 85 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1680 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/big-batch-soy-sesame-chicken-broccoli-669ecf1b46ae2b14647c3c9d
author: HelloFresh
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 8 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli{16%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}.

In a #medium pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1.5%cup}, 2 1/4 cups water (4 cups for 8), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Toss broccoli and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, salt, and @pepper{}; spread out in a single layer. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. (For 8 servings, use two baking sheets and roast on top and middle racks.)

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @soy sauce{4%tablespoon}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1%unit}, @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, 1/2 cup water, and @sugar{1/2%teaspoon} until smooth (use 1 cup water and 1 tsp sugar for 8 servings).

Open package of chicken and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat @sesame oil{1%tablespoon} and a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @diced chicken thighs{20%ounce} and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} (6-8 minutes for 8 servings).

Carefully add sauce to pan with chicken; stir to coat. Cook, stirring frequently, until sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Carefully transfer broccoli and onion to pan with saucy chicken. Add @bok choy and napa cabbage{4%ounce} and @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 8 servings). Stir until butter has melted and everything is coated in sauce.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to toss everything together in a large bowl for 8 servings.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with salt.

Transfer rice to a #large serving bowl{}. Transfer chicken and broccoli to a separate large serving bowl and garnish with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Serve family style.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.